\title{Iroh P2p}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{version}{1.0.0}

\meta{description}{Build modern peer-to-peer applications with Iroh. QUIC-based P2P networking, hole punching, content distribution, and decentralized data synchronization.}

\subtree{
\title{Iroh P2P Development}
\p{Build decentralized, peer-to-peer applications with \strong{Iroh} — a modern Rust P2P library based on QUIC with automatic hole punching, relay fallback, and content distribution.}

\subtree{
\title{What is Iroh?}
\p{Iroh is a \strong{nextgen P2P library} that implements:}

\ul{
\li{🔗 \strong{Direct P2P connections} via QUIC (UDP-based, faster than TCP)}
\li{🔄 \strong{Automatic hole punching} (NAT traversal without complexity)}
\li{📡 \strong{Relay fallback} (works even behind restrictive firewalls)}
\li{📦 \strong{Content distribution} (iroh-blobs for KB-TB transfers)}
\li{📝 \strong{Document sync} (iroh-docs for collaborative state)}
\li{💬 \strong{Gossip protocol} (iroh-gossip for message broadcasting)}
}

\p{\strong{Iroh represents data sovereignty}: users control their own nodes, direct connections replace central servers, and data stays decentralized.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Quick Start Project}
\subtree{
\title{1. Initialize Iroh Project}
\pre{\startverb
cargo new my_p2p_app
cd my_p2p_app

# Add dependencies
cargo add iroh@0.13
cargo add tokio --features full
cargo add anyhow
cargo add tracing tracing-subscriber
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{2. Create a Basic P2P Node}
\pre{\startverb
use anyhow::Result;

#[tokio::main]
async fn main() -> Result<()> {
    // Spawn an Iroh node with all services
    let node = iroh::node::Builder::default()
        .spawn()
        .await?;

    println!("✅ P2P node started!");
    println!("  📦 Blobs:  Available");
    println!("  📝 Docs:   Available");
    println!("  💬 Gossip: Available");

    // Keep running
    println!("\n⏳ Running... (Ctrl+C to stop)");
    tokio::signal::ctrl_c().await?;
    println!("👋 Shutting down...");

    Ok(())
}
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{3. Build and Run}
\pre{\startverb
cargo build --release
./target/release/my_p2p_app
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Core Concepts}
\subtree{
\title{Node Identity}
\p{Every Iroh node has a \strong{node ID} (public key) that other peers can connect to:}

\pre{\startverb
// Access node ID through services
let node_id = node.blobs.node_id().await?;
println!("My node ID: {}", node_id);

// Share this with other peers to establish connections
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Services}
\p{Iroh provides modular services you can use independently:}

\subtree{
\title{📦 iroh-bytes (Content Distribution)}
\p{Transfer files/blobs between peers (KB to TB):}

\pre{\startverb
// Publish a blob
let hash = node.blobs.add_bytes(b"Hello, P2P!").await?;

// Access via peer's node ID
let peer_id = "..."; // from other peer
let content = node.blobs.get_bytes(hash).await?;
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{📝 iroh-docs (Document Sync)}
\p{Sync structured data between peers with conflict-free resolution:}

\pre{\startverb
// Create a document (CRDT-based)
let doc = node.docs.create().await?;

// Write data
doc.set_bytes(b"key", b"value").await?;

// Other peers auto-sync
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{💬 iroh-gossip (Message Broadcasting)}
\p{Broadcast messages across a P2P network (publish/subscribe):}

\pre{\startverb
// Subscribe to a topic
let topic = "alerts".as_bytes();
let mut sub = node.gossip.subscribe(topic.clone()).await?;

// Publish a message
node.gossip.publish(topic.clone(), b"New alert!").await?;

// Receive messages
while let Ok(msg) = sub.next().await {
    println!("Received: {}", String::from_utf8_lossy(&msg));
}
\stopverb}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Architecture Patterns}
\subtree{
\title{Pattern 1: Direct Peer Connections}
\p{Connect to a peer by their node ID:}

\pre{\startverb
// Dial a peer directly
let peer_id = "..."; // node ID of another peer
let connection = node.net.connect(peer_id).await?;

// Use connection for RPC, streaming, etc.
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Pattern 2: Distributed Content Discovery}
\p{Use Iroh's DHT (Distributed Hash Table) for peer discovery:}

\pre{\startverb
// Announce your content
let hash = node.blobs.add_bytes(data).await?;

// Other peers query DHT to find providers
// Iroh handles this automatically
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Pattern 3: Relay Fallback}
\p{When direct connections fail (firewall), Iroh falls back to relays:}

\pre{\startverb
// Configured automatically - no code needed
// If direct connection fails → relay takes over
// User experiences seamless P2P
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Real-World Patterns}
\subtree{
\title{1. File Sync Between Two Peers}
\pre{\startverb
// Peer A: Share a file
let path = "/path/to/file.txt";
let bytes = std::fs::read(path)?;
let hash = node.blobs.add_bytes(&bytes).await?;
println!("Share this hash: {}", hash);

// Peer B: Receive the file
let hash = "..."; // from Peer A
let bytes = node.blobs.get_bytes(hash).await?;
std::fs::write("/path/to/downloaded.txt", bytes)?;
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{2. Live Collaboration (Docs + Gossip)}
\pre{\startverb
// Create shared document
let doc = node.docs.create().await?;

// Publish document ID via gossip
let doc_id = doc.id().to_string();
node.gossip.publish(b"shared_docs", doc_id.as_bytes()).await?;

// All peers subscribe and sync the doc
// Concurrent edits merge automatically (CRDT)
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{3. Distributed Cache}
\pre{\startverb
// Cache data in blobs, announce via gossip
let cache_entry = serde_json::to_vec(&data)?;
let hash = node.blobs.add_bytes(&cache_entry).await?;

// Broadcast availability
node.gossip.publish(b"cache_updates", hash.as_ref()).await?;

// Peers can fetch via hash
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Deployment Considerations}
\subtree{
\title{1. NAT/Firewall Handling}
\p{Iroh handles NAT traversal automatically:}

\pre{\startverb
// Your node automatically:
// ✓ Detects if behind NAT (via STUN)
// ✓ Attempts hole punching
// ✓ Falls back to relays if needed
// → No manual configuration required
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{2. Persistent Storage}
\p{Choose a storage backend:}

\pre{\startverb
// In-memory (default, for testing)
let node = iroh::node::Builder::default()
    .spawn()
    .await?;

// Persistent storage (recommended)
let node = iroh::node::Builder::default()
    .data_dir("/path/to/data")
    .spawn()
    .await?;
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{3. Relay Servers}
\p{Use public relays (can self-host):}

\pre{\startverb
// Iroh provides public relays
// Or run your own relay:
// https://github.com/n0-computer/iroh/tree/main/iroh-relay
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Security}
\subtree{
\title{1. Encryption by Default}
\p{All Iroh connections use TLS 1.3 with perfect forward secrecy:}

\pre{\startverb
// No extra code needed - automatic
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{2. Peer Authentication}
\p{Peers are identified by their \strong{node ID} (public key):}

\pre{\startverb
// Only trust specific peer IDs
let trusted_peer = "...";
if connection.peer_id() == trusted_peer {
    // Process message
}
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{3. Access Control}
\p{Implement application-level authorization:}

\pre{\startverb
// Docs can have per-key permissions
doc.set_bytes_with_author(
    author_key,
    key,
    value,
).await?;
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Performance Tuning}
\subtree{
\title{1. QUIC Configuration}
\pre{\startverb
// Iroh uses Quinn (QUIC implementation)
// Sensible defaults for most use cases
// Customize if needed:
// - Connection timeout
// - Max streams
// - MTU size
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{2. Batch Operations}
\pre{\startverb
// Efficient blob operations
let hashes = futures::stream::iter(data)
    .then(|item| async move {
        node.blobs.add_bytes(&item).await
    })
    .collect::<Vec<_>>()
    .await;
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{3. Content Addressing}
\pre{\startverb
// Use content hashes for deduplication
// Same content = same hash → no duplication
let hash1 = node.blobs.add_bytes(b"data").await?;
let hash2 = node.blobs.add_bytes(b"data").await?;
assert_eq!(hash1, hash2); // Same content address
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Testing}
\subtree{
\title{Local Network Testing}
\pre{\startverb
# Run multiple nodes locally for testing

# Terminal 1
RUST_LOG=debug cargo run -- --bind 127.0.0.1:0

# Terminal 2
RUST_LOG=debug cargo run -- --bind 127.0.0.1:0

# Nodes discover and connect automatically via DHT
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Integration Testing}
\pre{\startverb
#[tokio::test]
async fn test_p2p_transfer() {
    let node_a = iroh::node::Builder::default().spawn().await.unwrap();
    let node_b = iroh::node::Builder::default().spawn().await.unwrap();

    // Transfer data between nodes
    let data = b"test data";
    let hash = node_a.blobs.add_bytes(data).await.unwrap();

    let retrieved = node_b.blobs.get_bytes(hash).await.unwrap();
    assert_eq!(retrieved, data);
}
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Common Patterns & Best Practices}
\pre{\startverb
| Pattern | Use Case | Example |
|---------|----------|---------|
| **Blob Transfer** | File sync, backups | Share files without server |
| **Doc Sync** | Collaborative editing | Real-time document updates |
| **Gossip** | Notifications, feeds | Broadcast events to all peers |
| **Hybrid** | Complex apps | Combine all three services |
\stopverb}

\subtree{
\title{Best Practices}
\ol{
\li{\strong{Always handle errors gracefully} — Network is unreliable}
\li{\strong{Use persistent storage} — Don't lose data between restarts}
\li{\strong{Implement exponential backoff} — For retries}
\li{\strong{Test with firewalls} — Ensure relay fallback works}
\li{\strong{Monitor bandwidth} — P2P apps can use significant resources}
\li{\strong{Secure peer IDs} — Verify before trusting}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Troubleshooting}
\subtree{
\title{"Failed to dial peer"}
\p{Usually means relay fallback is needed:}

\pre{\startverb
// Iroh handles this automatically
// Check logs: RUST_LOG=debug
// If persistent, peer may be offline
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{High Latency}
\p{Could be relay usage (slower than direct):}

\pre{\startverb
# Check direct connection vs relay
RUST_LOG=iroh_net=debug
# Look for "direct" vs "relay" in logs
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Storage Growing}
\p{Blobs are content-addressed and immutable:}

\pre{\startverb
// Remove old blobs manually if needed
node.blobs.remove(hash).await?;
\stopverb}
}
}

